r lsa pre session course packages on mac installing packages on macos x up start by opening r and selecting the package installer from the packages & data menu r will pop open a window entitled r package installer there should be a dropdown with cran binaries selected if not select that click on the get list button next r will pop open a dialog to select a mirror pick one near you and hit ok finally we can install packages be sure the binary format packages and install dependencies buttons are checked find the packages xtable design hmisc languager lme4 e1071 and vr and click on each to select it while holding command aka apple or the cloverleaf and shift in order to select multiple packages at the same time click on install selected and wait r will download the packages it needs and then install them when it's done it will drop back to a prompt
